en..instructions: Rank the functions by order of growth, from the lowest rate of growth to the highest rate of growth. Note that if the functions are used to measure running time, then low rates of growth correspond to faster running times for large N, so that f<sub>1</sub>(N) < f<sub>2</sub>(N) < ... < f<sub>10</sub>(N).
